= form_for @page, url: create_page_url do |form|
  %fieldset.form-group
    = form.label :name
    %small.text-muted Required
    = form.text_field :name, class: "form-control"
  %fieldset.form-group
    = form.label :permalink
    %small.text-muted Optional
    %details
      %div
        By default, this is generated from the page <code>Name</code> by the following process:
        %ul
          %li
            Transliterating: Converting non-ASCII characters to ACSII. For example, <code>Ã¼</code> |
            becomes <code>u</code>.
          %li
            Parameterizing: Converting to lower case, replacing spaces with a <code>-</code>, and    |
            removing any characters that are not included within <code>a-z</code>, <code>0-9</code>, |
            or one of <code>-_</code>.
        Any value given here will undergo this same process.
    = form.text_field :permalink, class: "form-control"
  %fieldset.form-group
    = form.label :content_markdown
    %small.text-muted Required
    = form.text_area :content_markdown, class: "form-control"
  %fieldset.form-group
    = form.submit class: "btn btn-primary pull-right"
